<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="quoteright" style="width:350px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:56%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/bad_days_collage_6528.jpg" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/bad_days_collage_6528.jpg" width="350" height="196"></div></div><p></p><div class="indent"><em>Hey, don't worry, kid. Everyone has a bad day. Chin up.</em><div class="indent">&mdash; <strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/StanLee" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/StanLee">Stan Lee</a></strong>, Episode #1: <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SpiderMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SpiderMan">Spider-Man</a></em></div></div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p><em>Bad Days</em> is an animated series created by Junaid Chundrigar and Davor Bujakovic. The cartoons feature different fictional heroes and villains...on one of the worst days of their lives. There's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SilenceIsGolden" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SilenceIsGolden">almost no dialogue</a> involved, just hilarious situations and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut">Shout Outs</a> galore.</p><p>The series started with one short, <em><a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kollv82D2ns">Disassembled<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></em>, depicting several little mishaps in the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/MarvelUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/MarvelUniverse">Marvel Universe</a>. The short became a viral success, even appealing to former Marvel writer <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/StanLee" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/StanLee">Stan Lee</a>. He enlisted Junaid and Davor to make more cartoons for him to post on his <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/user/worldofheroes">World of Heroes<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube">YouTube</a> channel, later renamed MarvelousTV. The show also extended out to starring characters not owned by Marvel, and even characters who originated in media other than comic books.</p><p>As of season three, new cartoons appeared every other Saturday on the YouTube channel <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/user/CineFix">CineFix<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, instead of World of Heroes. Junaid and Davor also released commentaries in between. <em>Bad Days</em> returned to MarvelousTV for its fourth season, produced without Junaid, Davor, or the late Stan.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="toggleAllFolders();">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;open/close all folders&nbsp; </div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder0');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Season 1 Episodes&nbsp;</div><div id="folder0" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <em>Disassembled</em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kollv82D2ns">Episode 0<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/SpiderMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/SpiderMan">Spider-Man</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QjS6e9_F7B0">Episode 1<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/FantasticFour" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/FantasticFour">Fantastic Four</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_JpLYtCQHwA">Episode 2<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/GreenLantern" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/GreenLantern">Green Lantern</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IwNmQTpAc2w">Episode 3<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Superman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Superman">Superman</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yRGyWAT6UA4">Episode 4<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/XMen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/XMen">X-Men</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=72KNsrBmKOs">Episode 5<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Hellboy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Hellboy">Hellboy</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zA_PC9MIUlE">Episode 6<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheMightyThor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheMightyThor">The Mighty Thor</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4rp90osMpu8">Episode 7<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/CaptainAmerica" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/CaptainAmerica">Captain America</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qjQjTFc9U30">Episode 8<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Batman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Batman">Batman</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fe3t_YEh55k">Episode 9<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/IncredibleHulk" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/IncredibleHulk">Incredible Hulk</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xjKoljQRC5Q">Episode 10<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/IronMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/IronMan">Iron Man</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kn8R1IvFqKs">Episode 11<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheAvengers" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheAvengers">The Avengers</a></em>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bryaoVgIr1E">Episode 12<img sr